<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0"/>
    <title>Profile | TechFlow</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/stylesheets/profileAddStyle.css" />
    <link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Inter:wght@400;500;600;700&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">
</head>
<body>
    <div class="container">
        <!-- Profile Header -->
        <div class="profile-header">
            <div class="user-info">
                <div class="avatar">
                    <span></span>
                </div>
                <div>
                    <h1> <%= user.name %></h1>
                    <p class="username"><%= user.email %></p>
                    <!-- <p class="bio">Full-stack developer | Coffee addict | Building cool things</p> -->
                </div>
            </div>
            <a href="/mainprofile" class="new-post-btn">+ New Post</a>
        </div>

        <!-- Posts Section -->
        <div class="posts-container">
            <h2>Your Posts</h2>

            <!-- Sample Post 1 -->
            <div class="post-card">
                <div class="post-header">
                    <h3 class="post-title">My First Day with Node.js</h3>
                    <span class="post-date">Nov 10, 2025</span>
                </div>
                <p class="post-content">
                    Today I started learning Node.js and Express. It's amazing how easy it is to build a backend server! I created my first API route and connected it to MongoDB. Feeling excited!
                </p>
                <div class="post-actions">
                    <a href="#" class="like-btn">Like (12)</a>
                    <a href="#" class="edit-btn">Edit</a>
                </div>
            </div>

            <!-- Sample Post 2 -->
            <div class="post-card">
                <div class="post-header">
                    <h3 class="post-title">Why I Love Tailwind CSS</h3>
                    <span class="post-date">Nov 8, 2025</span>
                </div>
                <p class="post-content">
                    No more writing tons of CSS! With Tailwind, I can style directly in HTML and ship faster. The utility-first approach changed how I think about design systems.
                </p>
                <div class="post-actions">
                    <a href="#" class="like-btn">Like (8)</a>
                    <a href="#" class="edit-btn">Edit</a>
                </div>
            </div>

            <!-- Sample Post 3 -->
            <div class="post-card">
                <div class="post-header">
                    <h3 class="post-title">Deploying to Vercel in 2 Minutes</h3>
                    <span class="post-date">Nov 5, 2025</span>
                </div>
                <p class="post-content">
                    Just pushed my project to GitHub and connected it to Vercel. One click â†’ live in seconds! The preview URLs for pull requests are a game-changer for team workflows.
                </p>
                <div class="post-actions">
                    <a href="#" class="like-btn">Like (15)</a>
                    <a href="#" class="edit-btn">Edit</a>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Logout -->
        <div class="logout">
            <a href="/logout">Logout</a>
        </div>
    </div>
</body>
</html>